POVERTY WAGES ARE TOXIC Holly Sklar, AlterNet If your image of the typical minimum wage worker is a teenager, think again. Think of adult women working at checkout counters and in childcare, of healthcare aides taking care of your parents or grandparents -- without employer health benefits, paid sick days or paid vacation. A $5.15 minimum wage -- $10,712 a year -- just doesn't add up.  urlLink http://www.alternet.org/story.html?StoryID=16265